==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Combustion chamber
<hw>Com*bus"tion cham`ber</hw>. <fld>(Mech.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A
space over, or in front of, a boiler furnace where the gases from the
fire become more thoroughly mixed and burnt.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The
clearance space in the cylinder of an internal combustion engine where
the charge is compressed and ignited.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Combustious</ent>⟦br⟧
